  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM4.4.8">
<l>cilampiṉiṭaic ciṟuparalpōl periya mēru tirukkuḷampil kaṇakaṇappat tiruvā kāram</l>
<l>kuluṅkanila maṭantaitaṉai yiṭantu pulkik kōṭṭiṭaivait taruḷiyaveṅ kōmāṉ kaṇṭīr</l>
<l>ilaṅkiyanāṉ maṟaiyaṉaittu maṅka māṟu mēḻicaiyuṅ kēḷvikaḷu meṇṭik keṅkum</l>
<l>cilampiyanaṟ peruñcelan tikaḻum nāṅkūrt tiruteṟṟi yampalatteṉ ceṅkaṇ mālē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Our king who granted grace, digging up lady earth [and] embracing [her],</l>
<l rend="indent">placing [her] on his curved tusks,</l>
<l>So that Tiru’s body was shaken and so great [Mount] Meru rattled</l>
<l rend="indent">at his divine hoof like a little pebble inside an anklet, you see,</l>
<l>Is my bright-eyed Māl in Tirutteṟṟiyampalam in Nānkūr</l>
<l rend="indent">where great and fine riches shine,</l>
<l>[And] where everywhere in the eight directions resound</l>
<l rend="indent">the seven music [modes], [sacred] learning, six branches [of knowledge],</l>
<l rend="indent">and all of the four glorious Vedas.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
